{
  "texts": [
    "An effective pipelined implementation requires layers of the transformer models to be executed simultaneously.",
    "ReRAMs perform in situ MAC operations and necessitate the MHA and FF pre-trained weights on separate cores for pipelining [38].",
    "Conversely, there is no such requirement for systolic arrays.",
    "It can load parameters to execute computational kernels within a pipeline stage.",
    "Since ReRAM is utilized for most of the matrix operations, and systolic array is employed to perform only dynamic computations; a pipelined design requires more ReRAM cores compared to systolic array cores."
  ]
}